title: Grateful Dead Live at Long Beach Arena on 1980-12-14
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea-> Little Red Rooster*, Loser, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Bird Song, Passenger, Candyman-> Looks Like Rain-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Cold Rain & Snow-> Samson & Delilah, It Must Have Been The Roses, Estimated Prophet-> The Wheel-> Drums**-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around*-> Good Lovin', E: Brokedown Palace

*W Matt Kelley **W Airto & Flora Purim

reviews.review_text: Very good 1980 show Surprised no one has reviewed this source. Clear, crisp SBD, much better than the AUD's out there (and I like AUDs). Nice song selection for the period, well played, good energy; only flaw is a butchered Stella, which Jerry makes up for by jamming extra long and hard at the end. Highlights are the Estimated>Wheel>Drums>Space (with Flora Purim making creepy noises)>Other One which has some intense jamming.

Lesh! Philln up the phillin! Great soundin board. Seems to me lesh had alot to do with making a good show great. Lesh is more or something like that? Theyre all about it on this night,in non repeatable history for sure. The other one is  bout as good as it gets.(IMHO).Wharf Rat left a crater in my mind. Enjoy ya'll!

I was all night runnin'..Lord I wondered if you cared Nice sound here..Listen to the inner play between Jerry and Bobby on the Bertha> into Greatest Story..TEST ME TEST!! LOVE IT!! LBC IN THE HOUSE..and on through a very tight 1st set..everyone seems to be on their A game! Caries on into the 2nd set.. love the Must of Been the Doses!! The set ends with a smokin' Good Lovin' with one of my personal favorite encores Brokedown Palace..1980 had some really nice shows and here is one..so please>GIVE IT A WHIRL!!!!!! Forever Grateful>Forever Dead..LIFER!!

I am gonna sit right here until I die Very good sound. Well played!
Generous amount of diverse tunes 1st set.
(Rooster really comes to life with Matt Kelly)
Cali- laid back and mellow in full effect.
Stellar Stella Blue All the pieces fall perfectly into place on this night for this Stella Blue. I can not find another that comes as close to perfection. Thank you boys!
GREAT!!!!! I had an Aud. Recording of this for many many years. The Bertha guitar solo is imho one of the best I’ve heard. This is the first time I’ve heard the sbd. Very Good
